\vec {r} = f(\theta) \vec {u} \quad (I)
\vec {u}= \cos(\theta)\vec {i} +\sin(\theta) \vec {j}
\vec {v}= \dfrac{d\vec{u}}{d\theta} = -\sin(\theta)\vec {i} +\cos(\theta) \vec {j}
\vec {t} = \dfrac{d\vec{r}}{d\theta}.
